(Decision
    "Signal architecture rests on a three-layer model affirmed 2026-05-20: (1) Contract Operation — external request language, owned by signal-* contract crates (LedgerOperation, SpiritOperation, etc.); (2) Component Command — internal executable language, owned by each daemon (LedgerCommand, SpiritCommand, etc.), carrying the typed payloads its engine needs (Entry, ReadPlan, EventRecord, EntryKey); (3) Sema Operation — universal, PAYLOADLESS state-action classification (Assert / Mutate / Retract / Match / Subscribe / Validate) used ONLY for cross-component observation and introspection, not for execution. Component Commands project to Sema via a ToSemaOperation trait. Each daemon owns its CommandExecutor. The engine layer becomes a reusable framework parameterized over the component's Command type — atomic boundaries, snapshots, redb transaction handling are common; executable Command vocabulary is component-local."
    "Yes. That is the correct correction, and it supersedes my earlier 'payload-bearing SemaOperation' phrasing."
    "Affirming the three-layer model after designer/operator convergence. Substantive architectural shift from 'Sema as universal execution language' to 'Sema as universal classification language; execution is per-component.' Supersedes earlier intent records and skill text framing Sema/Signal as the typed database-operation language for execution."
    Maximum
    2026-05-20T02:00:00Z)

(Decision
    "skills/contract-repo.md and related skills must replace the earlier 'Signal is the workspace's typed binary database-operation language used to communicate' framing — that line is ambiguous under the three-layer model. The new framing: Signal carries typed contract messages; Sema names the universal state-action classes used for observation and introspection; executable database commands are component-local typed records owned by each daemon."
    "Designer is right that the skill text must change … Signal carries typed contract messages. Sema names the universal state-action classes used for observation and introspection. Executable database commands are component-local typed records owned by each daemon."
    "Skill-text supersession driven by the three-layer affirmation. Update needed in skills/contract-repo.md §'Signal is the database language', possibly skills/language-design.md and component-triad.md, plus ARCH files in signal-sema and signal-executor."
    Maximum
    2026-05-20T02:00:00Z)

(Decision
    "AcceptedOutcome::BatchAborted carries generic execution metadata, not contract-domain detail. Required fields: retry classification (Retryable | NotRetryable | Unknown) and commit status (NotCommitted | Unknown | Partial). Specific engine error types stay daemon-side; the wire reply carries enough generic metadata that retry/escalation policy can decide without knowing the concrete engine error. Total opacity (just 'EngineRejected' with no metadata) is too opaque; typed engine errors crossing the wire would force every contract to know engine internals."
    "BatchAborted { reason: EngineUnavailable, retry: Retryable, commit: NotCommitted }"
    "Refining /246-v3 hole 1 engine-failure path per operator clarification. Generic metadata is workspace-universal infrastructure; not contract-domain."
    Maximum
    2026-05-20T02:00:00Z)

(Decision
    "Tap/Untap is mandatory for persona components, no author override. Persona components reserve the same observability surface; persona-introspect has zero per-daemon vocabulary learning. Domain contracts that want a verb named Tap must rename their domain verb, not override the observability verb. Non-persona small utilities don't declare an observable block at all; they have no observability surface. Mandatory means mandatory SUPPORT (every persona component declares the observable block and emits when subscribed); runtime emission/storage cost is paid only when there's a subscriber."
    "Tap(ObserverFilter) Untap(ObserverSubscriptionToken) should be mandatory for Persona components."
    "Refining /246-v3 hole 2 + 4 per operator clarification. Standardize hard for persona; opt-out only by being a non-persona utility."
    Maximum
    2026-05-20T02:00:00Z)

(Decision
