    "Whether Mind needs explicit Start/Stop/Drain/Reload lifecycle verbs on its owner signal is itself an open question — possibly handled out-of-band by the infrastructure supervisor (systemd / spawn envelope / signals) rather than carried on `owner-signal-persona-mind`. The owner contract may stay cognitive-policy-only (Configure/Inspect and the Spirit-shaped surfaces that emerge), with lifecycle living in the supervisor's infrastructure layer."
    "we need star/stop/etc verbs?"
    "Psyche flagging uncertainty on whether Mind lifecycle verbs belong on a signal contract at all. The question opens a research direction rather than settling one way."
