(Constraint
    "A component CLI is only a thin client for its daemon: it translates the one NOTA argument into typed Signal frames, sends them to the daemon socket selected for that request, and translates typed Signal replies back to NOTA. It does not own state, mint daemon-owned fields, or perform component logic."
    "Make sure the CLI is only a client for the daemon and doesn't do anything else. And because that's an invariant for all of our components, the CLI doesn't do anything, it's just a thin client to speak the signal."
    "Restating the universal component CLI invariant while fixing persona-spirit's timestamp ownership."
