    2026-05-20 21:53)

(Clarification
    "Component CLIs need typed request-to-socket dispatch between the working socket and owner socket. The likely durable form is a generated Signal CLI layer that uses compile-time request-head knowledge from both contracts to choose the socket."
    "we have a designer working on a macro, a signal CLI macro, I think he called it, to write signal CLI micro, takes both contracts and emits the CLI with a compile time ahead identifier to socket dispatch table. Because we need to figure out which socket each command is going to, the owner socket or the normal socket."
    "Clarifying the CLI dispatch problem during the persona-spirit timestamp-ownership correction. The exact macro design belongs to the designer lane, but the direction affects Spirit's CLI conformance."
