(Decision
    "Component CLIs use a generated Signal CLI dispatch layer rather than bespoke routing code. The generated layer takes the working and owner contracts, derives a compile-time request-head-to-socket table, rejects ambiguous heads, and routes each single NOTA argument to either the working socket or the owner socket."
    "implement the cli macro described in reports/designer-assistant/129-mind-orchestrate-payload-and-cli-dispatch-option-a-2026-05-20.md ... develop the owner-signal contract with enough material (relevant material) to test the two-socket cli routing behavior"
    "Durable CLI architecture extracted from the persona-spirit generated CLI request. The implementation directive itself is not intent; the persistent rule is that dispatch is generated from both contracts and proves two-socket routing."
    Maximum
    2026-05-20T22:27:40+02:00)

(Decision
    "Component runtime flakes expose the thin CLI and the daemon as separate installable packages. The split lets the CLI be installed into a user's profile independently from the long-lived daemon package."
    "then when its all working, split the two (daemon and cli) packages in the nix flake, so its ready to be incorporated in my nix profile"
    "Persistent packaging rule from the persona-spirit CLI macro request. This is more than the one task because it applies to every component triad's install surface."
